03:07.945 --> 03:11.917
♪♪

03:15.053 --> 03:16.954
(PAN THUDS)

03:25.730 --> 03:27.831
Crap.

03:27.832 --> 03:30.001
Ugh.

03:36.874 --> 03:39.478
(JARS CLINKING)

03:51.621 --> 03:53.756
(INSECTS CHIRPING)

03:53.757 --> 03:59.697
(JANGLING)

04:02.667 --> 04:06.771
♪♪

04:07.083 --> 04:08.851
She gon' come sit with us?

04:09.406 --> 04:11.169
I have no idea.

04:13.377 --> 04:14.678
Okay.

04:14.679 --> 04:16.612
Well, I just wanted to let y'all know

04:16.613 --> 04:18.882
that Trey Willis is getting
out on bond today.

04:20.050 --> 04:22.118
Why would you need to tell us that?

04:22.119 --> 04:24.855
I know there's been a
lot of talk around town

04:24.856 --> 04:27.523
in regards to what
Trey did or didn't do.

04:27.524 --> 04:29.993
As far as killing George?

04:29.994 --> 04:31.994
Among other things.

04:31.995 --> 04:33.698
Like raping my sister?

04:35.699 --> 04:37.985
It's all gonna come out
in the trial, Bobby.

04:39.169 --> 04:40.791
Sounds familiar.

04:42.125 --> 04:45.042
I just don't want you to do
anything that you would regret.

04:45.653 --> 04:47.679
You wouldn't be so lucky this time.

04:48.228 --> 04:50.120
If Trey didn't kill you himself,

04:50.121 --> 04:51.772
he'd damn sure press charges.

04:53.495 --> 04:55.752
I ain't gonna do anything
to Trey or anybody else

04:55.753 --> 04:57.389
I haven't heard about yet.

04:59.157 --> 05:00.434
Okay.

05:01.691 --> 05:03.627
I'll take you at your word, then.

05:05.662 --> 05:07.138
But I do know this.

05:08.098 --> 05:09.866
I can't keep giving a shit forever

05:09.867 --> 05:11.535
like everyone else around here.

05:15.972 --> 05:18.472
You're not gonna say he
didn't do it, are you?

05:19.509 --> 05:20.802
Ma'am?

05:21.679 --> 05:23.331
Daniel Holden.

05:24.015 --> 05:25.115
At the end of all this,

05:25.116 --> 05:28.019
you're not gonna say he
didn't kill my baby, are you?

05:32.189 --> 05:33.289
I'm really sorry

05:33.290 --> 05:36.727
this is all getting stirred
up again for ya, ma'am.

05:46.102 --> 05:48.247
I wouldn't lose sleep
over that, Sheriff.

05:48.872 --> 05:50.240
She never quit stirring.

05:51.107 --> 05:53.011
Not one goddamn day.

05:56.983 --> 05:59.889
JANET: Hey, Daniel, it's your mama.

06:00.951 --> 06:02.519
Not much to say today,

06:02.520 --> 06:05.221
other than everybody
misses you terribly.

06:05.222 --> 06:06.623
(SIGHS)

06:06.624 --> 06:08.711
Let's see, Jared got a new bike.

06:09.547 --> 06:12.062
He isn't much interested in cars yet.

06:12.063 --> 06:13.596
Which is good. (CHUCKLES)

06:13.597 --> 06:15.130
Bikes are a lot cheaper.

06:15.665 --> 06:18.009
And your job sounds interesting, honey.

06:18.869 --> 06:21.082
You know, a good place to start.

06:21.806 --> 06:23.014
Proud of you.

06:25.008 --> 06:27.243
Anyway, call me again
if you get the chance.

06:27.244 --> 06:29.779
I promise to have the
phone near me next time.

06:29.780 --> 06:32.049
Uh, no pressure, though.

06:33.444 --> 06:34.864
We love you.

06:41.893 --> 06:45.964
(WATER TRICKLING)

06:49.226 --> 06:50.427
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

06:50.428 --> 06:53.129
(TAPE RIPPING)

06:53.130 --> 06:57.667
♪♪

06:57.668 --> 06:59.071
(SIGHS)

07:01.772 --> 07:06.411
(BIRD CHIRPING)

07:07.739 --> 07:09.205
Okay.

07:09.988 --> 07:12.527
Nobody's gonna be
completely happy with this.

07:12.957 --> 07:14.259
It's called a schedule.

07:16.045 --> 07:18.736
I took everyone's requests
into consideration,

07:18.737 --> 07:20.597
but there were some conflicts, so...

07:20.598 --> 07:21.811
Works for me.

07:21.812 --> 07:23.474
I got zilch going on.

07:24.318 --> 07:25.789
Well, that's great, Frank.

07:25.790 --> 07:26.992
Thanks.

07:29.373 --> 07:31.141
Uh, sorry.

07:31.142 --> 07:33.210
Peanut came to me first.

07:33.211 --> 07:37.016
♪♪

07:39.584 --> 07:40.985
(SCOFFS)

07:49.627 --> 07:51.263
Am I supposed to knock?

07:51.937 --> 07:54.300
Hell, no. Get in here.

07:58.303 --> 07:59.505
Take a load off.

08:03.141 --> 08:04.424
What?

08:05.406 --> 08:07.311
What she got going on on Thursday?

08:07.988 --> 08:10.480
Doctor's appointment,
post-something or other.

08:10.481 --> 08:11.515
Still?

08:11.516 --> 08:12.715
You saw that baby.

08:12.716 --> 08:14.551
- Gotta be collateral damage.
- (SIGHS)

08:14.552 --> 08:16.285
I have finals on Friday.

08:16.286 --> 08:17.487
You have Friday off.

08:17.488 --> 08:19.023
But not Thursday.

08:19.024 --> 08:20.224
What about Wednesday?

08:20.225 --> 08:22.326
The day before the day before finals?

08:22.327 --> 08:24.061
(SCOFFS) If I could
remember stuff that long,

08:24.062 --> 08:25.496
I wouldn't have to
cram the night before.

08:25.497 --> 08:27.564
All right, all right.

08:27.565 --> 08:28.968
I get it.

08:30.435 --> 08:31.634
What about Frank?

08:31.635 --> 08:32.802
Don't worry about it.

08:32.803 --> 08:34.955
Just do good on your tests.

08:36.349 --> 08:39.042
Superman does good. We do well.

08:40.857 --> 08:43.259
Are we still gonna smoke pot together?

08:43.561 --> 08:45.794
'Course... maybe.

08:45.795 --> 08:47.217
- That means no.
- (SIGHS)

08:47.218 --> 08:49.619
Just... let me figure out how
to make a schedule first.

08:49.620 --> 08:52.388
Then we can discuss our pot futures.

08:52.389 --> 08:53.557
Okay?

08:54.430 --> 08:56.093
You're doing great, you know.

08:56.784 --> 08:58.061
Right.

08:58.062 --> 08:59.162
I'm serious.

08:59.163 --> 09:02.007
Go, study, multiply.

09:02.800 --> 09:04.191
Yes, boss lady.

09:04.601 --> 09:05.803
(BOTH LAUGH)

09:05.804 --> 09:07.238
(DOOR CLOSES)

09:08.839 --> 09:11.408
Look, Jon, I know you've
become close to the family.

09:11.409 --> 09:12.809
It's not about that, Bernie.

09:12.810 --> 09:14.343
We all want our clients
to be exonerated.

09:14.344 --> 09:15.846
Of course we do.

09:15.847 --> 09:18.281
But more than that, we don't
want them to be executed,

09:18.282 --> 09:20.384
so we take plea deals,

09:20.385 --> 09:22.486
deals for time served, Alford pleas.

09:22.487 --> 09:24.088
Look, a win for us

09:24.089 --> 09:26.123
is a life not taken by
the state... period.

09:26.124 --> 09:28.458
But with this particular case, sir,

09:28.459 --> 09:29.693
if the plea deal had been offered

09:29.694 --> 09:31.727
just two days later, <i>one</i> day...

09:31.728 --> 09:33.664
With the events that
transpired in that time,

09:33.665 --> 09:36.333
I can guarantee you, my client
would not have taken the deal.

09:36.334 --> 09:38.096
That's unfortunate, Jon, truly.

09:38.097 --> 09:40.270
And with the additional information
that we've learned since then,

09:40.271 --> 09:41.538
I can almost guarantee you,

09:41.539 --> 09:43.607
the prosecution would
never dare retry him.

09:43.608 --> 09:46.477
Okay, Jon, since you won't take
"hell, no, absolutely not"

09:46.478 --> 09:47.678
for an answer,

09:47.679 --> 09:49.548
what are you talking about here?

09:51.315 --> 09:54.217
Just going down there
for a couple of weeks

09:54.218 --> 09:55.452
to further build the case.

09:55.453 --> 09:57.154
There is no case. It's over.

09:57.155 --> 09:59.289
You have four other
clients on death row,

09:59.290 --> 10:01.125
two toward the end of
their appeals process.

10:01.126 --> 10:02.963
They will not be neglected, sir.

10:02.964 --> 10:04.432
What's the end game here?

10:07.265 --> 10:08.665
I'm just looking at options.

10:08.666 --> 10:11.107
Please. There's only one option.

10:11.108 --> 10:12.504
Habeas corpus.

10:13.170 --> 10:15.238
You're... You're talking about
years of legal maneuvering,

10:15.239 --> 10:17.641
years of resources, of which
there are limits around here,

10:17.642 --> 10:19.476
for a guy who's already
out of friggin' jail.

10:19.477 --> 10:21.277
And even then, it's a long shot.

10:21.278 --> 10:22.411
- You know that as well as anyone.
- (SIGHS)

10:22.412 --> 10:24.256
If that were the criteria, sir...

10:24.257 --> 10:27.264
Post-conviction relief for
somebody already on probation?

10:27.972 --> 10:29.725
You got to get real, Jon.

10:31.602 --> 10:33.079
I know you're right.

10:33.880 --> 10:34.901
I do.

10:35.205 --> 10:37.668
Seven years is a lot of
your life to invest.

10:38.508 --> 10:39.724
It was, at that.

10:40.277 --> 10:41.645
And it's personal. It's always personal.

10:41.646 --> 10:42.967
We know that, too.

10:45.248 --> 10:46.434
But he's out.

10:47.421 --> 10:48.809
You got him out.

10:50.894 --> 10:52.723
You have to let it go now.

10:53.424 --> 10:55.360
(SIGHS)

10:57.966 --> 10:59.027
Of course.

10:59.396 --> 11:02.066
♪♪

11:03.568 --> 11:05.470
Um, thank you for listening.

11:10.507 --> 11:14.311
♪♪

11:17.548 --> 11:19.448
(DISHES CLATTER IN DISTANCE)

11:19.449 --> 11:22.385
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACH)

11:22.386 --> 11:23.553
Hello.

11:23.554 --> 11:26.755
Um, I'm here to meet... Oh.

11:26.756 --> 11:29.192
There he is. Thank you.

11:29.193 --> 11:30.360
I'm so sorry I'm late.

11:30.361 --> 11:31.394
No, it's all right.

11:31.395 --> 11:33.564
- (KEYS JINGLE)
- Um...

11:36.467 --> 11:39.435
Well, how you think
you did on your test?

11:39.436 --> 11:41.137
Oh, I don't know.

11:41.138 --> 11:43.206
Just glad it's over.

11:43.207 --> 11:45.141
I'll bet you did great.

11:45.142 --> 11:47.358
Like I've said, you're one smart gal.

11:47.359 --> 11:48.882
Thank you, Teddy.

11:48.883 --> 11:50.150
Have you ordered?

11:50.151 --> 11:51.680
Nah, I was just waiting on you.

11:51.681 --> 11:54.063
I hope you haven't been here too long.

11:54.064 --> 11:54.918
I'm sorry.

11:54.919 --> 11:56.486
Don't be.

11:56.487 --> 11:58.050
I got nowhere to go.

11:58.051 --> 11:59.255
Free as a lark.

12:00.251 --> 12:03.260
But I do. I have to be at
work in less than an hour.

12:03.840 --> 12:04.867
Sorry.

12:05.236 --> 12:07.164
Oh, why... why so early?

12:07.859 --> 12:11.233
There's a... a woman coming
in to show us how to...

12:11.234 --> 12:15.472
Uh, it's not exactly
dinner conversation.

12:15.473 --> 12:17.782
Oh, well, you got to tell me now.

12:18.642 --> 12:20.802
How to clip toenails on old people.

12:21.912 --> 12:23.523
You want some ketchup with that?

12:23.524 --> 12:24.514
(CHUCKLES)

12:24.515 --> 12:26.177
You asked.

12:29.773 --> 12:31.075
Y'all ready to order?

12:31.555 --> 12:33.722
Um, oh, can I take a quick look, please?

12:33.723 --> 12:35.525
Um, Teddy?

12:36.283 --> 12:36.959
Uh, yeah.

12:36.960 --> 12:39.696
Uh, hamburger, medium-well,
fries, Diet Coke.

12:40.502 --> 12:42.832
Uh, may I... I have a
Cobb salad, please?

12:42.833 --> 12:45.669
Uh, light on the blue
cheese, if they can,

12:45.670 --> 12:48.344
and just water, I guess.

12:52.330 --> 12:53.903
So, how was your week?

12:55.880 --> 12:58.981
Well, we got the county contract.

12:58.982 --> 13:00.583
What?

13:00.584 --> 13:02.718
No fanfare, just called
and said we got it.

13:02.719 --> 13:05.188
They're gonna be getting tires
from us the next 12 months.

13:05.189 --> 13:06.222
Rims, too.

13:06.223 --> 13:08.692
Wow, rims, too? That's great, Teddy.

13:08.693 --> 13:11.329
Well, like they say, you
stop chasing after it...

13:12.463 --> 13:16.399
Your... Your dad must be on cloud nine.

13:17.869 --> 13:21.078
Well, it's more like cloud three,
but it's nine for most people.

13:22.872 --> 13:26.854
Maybe things are... are
turning around, you know?

13:27.478 --> 13:29.213
At... At the store.

13:31.015 --> 13:32.314
(INHALES SHARPLY)

13:32.315 --> 13:34.527
Yup, I bet you aced that test.

13:35.934 --> 13:38.285
I think I did, be honest.

13:38.755 --> 13:40.335
That's great, Tawney.

13:40.993 --> 13:43.338
I even like studying.

13:43.884 --> 13:46.112
I like school. I get there early.

13:48.608 --> 13:51.690
I mean, I'm not saying it's not work.

13:52.159 --> 13:53.153
It's work.

13:53.662 --> 13:55.911
It's not like actual fun.

13:55.912 --> 14:00.155
Hey, you ain't got to make
something be what it's not for me.

14:00.719 --> 14:03.221
I mean, if you like something, enjoy it,

14:03.222 --> 14:05.121
then that's what it is, right?

14:05.931 --> 14:08.628
And if you can't tell me that,
then what the hell are we doing?

14:10.528 --> 14:12.028
You sound like Rebecca.

14:13.106 --> 14:14.827
It makes sense, you know.

14:16.275 --> 14:18.402
I still feel guilty sometimes.

14:18.403 --> 14:19.603
(ICE CLINKS)

14:19.604 --> 14:20.806
(GLASSES THUD)

14:22.672 --> 14:24.140
Enjoying things?

14:24.620 --> 14:26.074
That I'm staying at that big house

14:26.075 --> 14:28.729
and you're staying with...
at your daddy's...

14:28.730 --> 14:29.612
Hold it.

14:29.613 --> 14:31.885
I thought that subject was
off limits on date night.

14:32.715 --> 14:33.949
I can't remember.

14:33.950 --> 14:35.163
Probably.

14:41.157 --> 14:43.353
The main reason you're by yourself

14:43.993 --> 14:45.882
is so you can figure
out what you want...

14:46.664 --> 14:48.198
really want.

14:48.199 --> 14:49.866
And if you're always
feeling bad or guilty,

14:49.867 --> 14:51.568
how are you ever gonna know?

14:52.532 --> 14:53.952
Probably won't.

14:56.540 --> 14:58.666
I want you to thrive, Tawney.

14:59.576 --> 15:00.887
I really do.

15:01.771 --> 15:03.447
I know you do, Teddy.

15:04.982 --> 15:06.951
I want you to thrive, too.

15:09.920 --> 15:11.555
I know you do.

15:13.089 --> 15:17.894
(ICE RATTLING)

15:17.895 --> 15:19.628
(INSECTS CHIRPING)

15:19.629 --> 15:21.698
AMANTHA: I'm sorry, too, Dimitri.

15:21.699 --> 15:23.232
I'm very sorry.

15:23.233 --> 15:25.001
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

15:25.002 --> 15:29.808
The bomb, Dimitri... the hydrogen bomb.

15:35.879 --> 15:38.148
(EXHALES SHARPLY)

15:40.550 --> 15:44.521
♪♪

15:49.560 --> 15:55.199
(IMITATES EXPLOSION)

16:00.738 --> 16:04.541
(PAPER CRINKLES)

16:08.746 --> 16:09.968
Cool.

16:18.415 --> 16:20.249
(INSECTS CHIRPING)

16:20.250 --> 16:22.063
Good evening, Mr. Persinger.

16:22.083 --> 16:23.385
Hey, Tawney.

16:25.116 --> 16:26.316
Hey, y'all.

16:26.317 --> 16:28.050
- Hey, Mrs. Sutter.
- Hey, Tawney.

16:28.051 --> 16:29.119
Well?

16:29.120 --> 16:30.562
I don't know yet.

16:31.522 --> 16:33.090
Fingers crossed.

16:33.091 --> 16:35.792
Thank you, Mrs. Sutter. How
are your cards tonight?

16:35.793 --> 16:38.395
I hope you have better
luck on your test.

16:38.396 --> 16:39.540
(LAUGHS)

16:41.265 --> 16:43.130
I'll come by and check
on you a little later.

16:44.202 --> 16:47.610
You got the short straw... Zeke.

16:48.139 --> 16:49.505
How's he doing tonight?

16:49.506 --> 16:52.274
Dramatic as usual and extra pissy.

16:52.275 --> 16:55.946
Page me if there's any issues.
I'll get the on-call nurse.

16:56.979 --> 16:58.347
Have fun.

16:58.348 --> 16:59.421
Thank you.

17:14.298 --> 17:16.742
Mr. Zeke, it's Tawney.

17:17.688 --> 17:19.386
I'll be with you tonight.

17:20.915 --> 17:23.363
You had to wake me up to tell me that?

17:25.175 --> 17:26.376
I'm sorry.

17:27.148 --> 17:28.978
Can I get you anything right now?

17:28.979 --> 17:30.745
My plaque.

17:31.405 --> 17:33.850
Your... Your plaque?

17:33.851 --> 17:36.019
You don't have to talk loud.

17:36.020 --> 17:37.222
I'm not deaf.

17:41.440 --> 17:42.383
Uh...

17:43.127 --> 17:45.795
what... what plaque are
you talking about?

17:46.548 --> 17:49.865
I've told you all five times already.

17:49.866 --> 17:52.203
This would be my first time, sir.

17:54.939 --> 17:57.006
(RUSTLING)

17:57.007 --> 17:58.266
From the plant.

17:59.477 --> 18:01.479
35 years' worth.

18:03.547 --> 18:06.284
I want to have it with me when I go,

18:07.250 --> 18:09.787
which I'm praying is tonight.

18:12.055 --> 18:15.958
Well, can your... can your
nephew bring it for you?

18:15.959 --> 18:17.459
He lives in Arizona.

18:18.348 --> 18:19.703
Arizona?

18:21.622 --> 18:25.101
Is... Is there any other family nearby?

18:25.839 --> 18:27.772
My wife was barren.

18:28.570 --> 18:30.025
Wasn't her fault.

18:30.682 --> 18:31.941
Just was.

18:32.402 --> 18:35.546
♪♪

18:41.951 --> 18:44.146
(MACHINE BEEPS, WHIRRING)

18:44.147 --> 18:47.208
Well, what about neighbors or friends?

18:47.209 --> 18:48.925
Could they go get it for you?

18:48.926 --> 18:51.194
- We had a falling out.
- (MACHINE CLICKS)

18:51.195 --> 18:52.572
Who did?

18:54.068 --> 18:59.910
The key is in the mouth
of the horny toad

18:59.911 --> 19:03.473
next to the... the iron thing.

19:03.474 --> 19:05.909
(MACHINE HISSES, BEEPS)

19:05.910 --> 19:07.486
It's not real, of course.

19:08.979 --> 19:10.625
It's ceramic.

19:13.150 --> 19:14.383
(VELCRO TEARS)

19:14.384 --> 19:15.919
Blood pressure is a little low tonight.

19:15.920 --> 19:18.209
(RUSTLING)

19:20.712 --> 19:23.806
I'll come check on you
in a little while, okay?

19:27.248 --> 19:29.827
You're just like all the
rest of 'em, ain't you?

19:31.915 --> 19:33.084
What do you mean?

19:34.926 --> 19:36.061
Never mind.

19:36.801 --> 19:40.406
♪♪

19:44.342 --> 19:48.147
(THE FOUNDATIONS' <I>"BUILD
ME UP BUTTERCUP"</I> PLAYING)

19:51.815 --> 19:53.816
♪ Why do you build me up ♪

19:53.817 --> 19:54.985
<i>♪ Build me up ♪</i>

19:54.986 --> 19:56.352
♪ Buttercup, baby ♪

19:56.353 --> 19:58.788
♪ Just to let me down, let me down ♪

19:58.789 --> 19:59.890
♪ And push me around ♪

19:59.891 --> 20:01.225
♪ And then, worst of all ♪

20:01.226 --> 20:02.258
(VOLUME INCREASES) <i>♪ Worst of all ♪</i>

20:02.259 --> 20:03.526
♪ You never call, baby ♪

20:03.527 --> 20:05.896
♪ When you say you will, say you wil ♪

20:05.897 --> 20:07.296
♪ But I love you, still ♪

20:07.297 --> 20:08.931
- ♪ I need you ♪
- <i>♪ I need you ♪</i>

20:08.932 --> 20:10.900
♪ More than anyone, darling ♪

20:10.901 --> 20:14.470
♪ You know that I have
from the sta-a-rt ♪

20:14.471 --> 20:17.140
♪ So build me up, build
me up, buttercup ♪

20:17.141 --> 20:20.377
♪ Don't break my he-e-art ♪

20:20.378 --> 20:21.911
(BANGING, GLASS SHATTERING)

20:21.912 --> 20:24.415
(TIRES SQUEALING)

20:26.383 --> 20:27.551
- (CRASH)
- <i>♪...around and then ♪</i>

20:27.552 --> 20:29.352
- (GASPS)
- <i>♪ Ba-da-da ♪</i>

20:29.353 --> 20:31.420
<i>♪ I went to the door,
I can take anymore ♪</i>

20:31.421 --> 20:33.457
- (BREATHING HEAVILY)
- <i>♪ It's not you ♪</i>

20:33.458 --> 20:35.324
<i>♪ You let me down again ♪</i>

20:35.325 --> 20:36.860
- <i>♪ Hey, hey, hey ♪</i>
- (ENGINE CLICKING)

20:36.861 --> 20:38.961
<i>♪ Baby, baby, try to find ♪</i>

20:38.962 --> 20:40.063
<i>♪ Hey, hey, hey ♪</i>

20:40.064 --> 20:41.230
<i>♪ A little time ♪</i>

20:41.231 --> 20:42.900
<i>♪ And I'll make you mine ♪</i>

20:42.901 --> 20:44.436
- (ENGINE SHUTS OFF)
- (SIGHS)

20:45.969 --> 20:49.476
(CLICK, RAPID BEEPING)

20:49.477 --> 20:50.850
(CAR DOOR CLOSES)

20:52.544 --> 20:54.244
(SIGHS)

20:54.245 --> 20:56.314
(SIGHS DEEPLY)

20:57.949 --> 21:01.253
(GRAVEL CRUNCHING)

21:04.154 --> 21:06.758
(SIGHING)

21:12.229 --> 21:14.264
(BIRD CRIES)

21:14.265 --> 21:15.498
(GROANS)

21:15.499 --> 21:17.100
Buzzkill.

21:17.101 --> 21:20.906
♪♪

21:31.850 --> 21:34.285
Buzzkill times a bunch.

21:42.994 --> 21:44.728
TED SR.: Since when did
he like camping out?

21:46.296 --> 21:48.015
I don't know that he does.

21:49.255 --> 21:50.693
Well, it's just one night.

21:51.035 --> 21:52.362
I'm sure he'll be fine.

21:53.204 --> 21:56.237
(CELLPHONE RINGING)

21:57.627 --> 21:58.641
This is Ted.

21:58.642 --> 22:00.343
(THROUGH CELLPHONE)
<i>Hey (SIGHS) it's Amantha.</i>

22:00.344 --> 22:01.410
<i>I need your help.</i>

22:01.411 --> 22:02.880
What happened?

22:02.881 --> 22:05.948
My car broke down around
Clyetteville Road.

22:05.949 --> 22:08.017
- What are you doing way out there?
- What's wrong?

22:08.018 --> 22:09.285
(WHISPERS) It's Amantha.

22:09.286 --> 22:12.288
Just convening with nature, I guess.

22:12.289 --> 22:13.390
In the dark?

22:13.391 --> 22:14.735
What happened?

22:14.736 --> 22:16.916
<i>Well, it wasn't dark
when I was convening.</i>

22:17.262 --> 22:18.363
(SIGHS)

22:18.364 --> 22:20.030
Can't get phone service near the car,

22:20.031 --> 22:22.064
so I had to walk... half-mile, maybe?

22:22.065 --> 22:24.200
Well, just go back to
your car and wait there.

22:24.201 --> 22:25.235
I'm on my way.

22:25.236 --> 22:26.335
<i>Thank you, Big Ted.</i>

22:26.336 --> 22:27.371
Tell her to lock the doors.

22:27.372 --> 22:28.505
Lock the doors.

22:28.506 --> 22:30.306
- <i>Mama just say that?</i>
- Yep.

22:30.307 --> 22:32.310
- What'd she say?
- Yep.

22:33.311 --> 22:36.612
It was kind of scary, really,
but don't tell her that.

22:36.613 --> 22:37.579
Nope.

22:38.650 --> 22:40.082
I'll be there...

22:40.083 --> 22:41.618
<i>20, 30 minutes.</i>

22:41.619 --> 22:43.687
- Thank you, Big Ted.
- <i>Yep.</i>

22:44.354 --> 22:45.486
What happened?

22:46.123 --> 22:50.127
(INSECTS CHIRPING)

22:52.462 --> 22:56.267
(VEHICLE APPROACHING)

23:03.474 --> 23:07.279
♪♪

23:19.324 --> 23:20.730
MAN: Everything okay?

23:22.191 --> 23:23.896
Everything's fine.

23:25.569 --> 23:27.024
Didn't mean to scare you.

23:27.597 --> 23:29.214
Just seeing if you needed help.

23:30.601 --> 23:33.016
My boyfriend should be here any minute.

23:34.005 --> 23:35.209
Had car trouble.

23:38.924 --> 23:40.278
Thank you, though.

23:42.025 --> 23:43.080
Amantha?

23:44.145 --> 23:45.402
- (ENGINE REVS)
- It's Billy.

23:45.828 --> 23:47.362
Billy Harris.

23:48.599 --> 23:51.121
(SIGHS) Shit fire, Billy.

23:51.122 --> 23:52.522
- Sorry.
- (SIGHS DEEPLY)

23:52.523 --> 23:55.492
Kind of hard not to scare
someone in this situation.

23:55.493 --> 23:57.596
No shit.

23:59.321 --> 24:01.486
(INSECTS CHIRPING)

24:01.489 --> 24:03.457
Well, that's not good.

24:03.458 --> 24:04.624
(SCOFFS)

24:04.625 --> 24:06.534
Already had that much figured out.

24:10.498 --> 24:12.999
Where the hell'd you get
a flashlight that big?

24:13.000 --> 24:15.436
At the big-flashlight store.

24:17.171 --> 24:18.704
(FLASHLIGHT CLICKS OFF)

24:18.705 --> 24:20.442
Your boyfriend know anything about cars?

24:21.816 --> 24:22.831
No.

24:23.752 --> 24:27.012
I mean, I don't have a boyfriend.

24:27.755 --> 24:29.288
Oh, okay.

24:29.750 --> 24:31.420
It just sounded...

24:32.536 --> 24:34.820
I was a little unnerved
by the situation.

24:35.670 --> 24:37.421
Completely understandable.

24:40.551 --> 24:42.314
Is anybody coming?

24:43.097 --> 24:45.198
Yes, anybody's coming, Billy.

24:45.714 --> 24:46.967
My stepfather.

24:46.968 --> 24:48.312
Oh, well...

24:49.604 --> 24:52.204
Mr. Talbot can probably
tell you how bad it is.

24:52.205 --> 24:53.920
I'm sure.

24:55.696 --> 24:57.529
Well, I appreciate you stopping and all,

24:57.530 --> 24:58.871
but you don't have to stay.

24:58.872 --> 25:01.124
Ted'll be here any minute,
and I can just wait in the car.

25:02.616 --> 25:04.150
Might be small-town of me,

25:04.151 --> 25:06.786
but I ain't leaving a woman
by herself on some dark road

25:06.787 --> 25:08.814
until I am sure she's taken care of.

25:08.815 --> 25:10.336
Would you leave a man like that?

25:10.356 --> 25:11.838
Well, it depends on who it was.

25:12.734 --> 25:14.313
Now, I can go sit in my truck and wait

25:14.314 --> 25:15.647
if you prefer keeping your own company.

25:16.706 --> 25:18.460
God, you're still sensitive, aren't you?

25:18.461 --> 25:19.978
That's a trick question.

25:21.338 --> 25:22.881
I just didn't want to
put you out, Billy.

25:22.882 --> 25:25.434
- That's all.
- You're not putting me out.

25:25.435 --> 25:28.003
I'm recording the game, got
venison in the Crock-Pot.

25:28.004 --> 25:30.137
God, I don't know how you can wait.

25:35.346 --> 25:36.450
I'm sorry.

25:36.946 --> 25:39.430
It's a bad habit.

25:39.734 --> 25:41.144
No skin off my back.

25:49.212 --> 25:51.181
(SIGHS)

25:53.049 --> 25:55.267
So, are you still cutting
grass and stuff?

25:55.268 --> 25:56.284
Yep.

25:56.285 --> 25:58.553
Still in the landscaping business.

25:58.554 --> 25:59.988
I... (SIGHS)

25:59.989 --> 26:02.924
I didn't mean that sound
like, you know, a putdown.

26:02.925 --> 26:04.760
I didn't take it that way.

26:04.761 --> 26:06.997
Grass needs cutting, leaves need raking.

26:08.998 --> 26:10.785
You still working at Thrifty Town?

26:12.128 --> 26:13.601
How'd you know that?

26:14.105 --> 26:15.838
You're back in Paulie, Dorothy.

26:16.526 --> 26:17.349
Right.

26:17.839 --> 26:19.780
Yeah, still there...

26:20.208 --> 26:21.809
after all these months.

26:21.810 --> 26:23.946
(VEHICLE APPROACHING)

26:28.885 --> 26:30.218
Do I look stoned?

26:30.219 --> 26:31.494
I'm sorry?

26:33.056 --> 26:34.573
I withdraw the question.

26:35.005 --> 26:36.892
I'd say you're safe,

26:36.893 --> 26:38.847
unless you, like, lead with that.

26:41.840 --> 26:43.130
You sure that's him?

26:43.131 --> 26:45.200
Uh, not yet.

26:45.201 --> 26:47.595
Don't worry. If it's not, I'm packing.

26:48.660 --> 26:51.005
- You are not packing.
- Okay.

26:51.006 --> 26:52.674
If you're packing,
Billy, you're an idiot.

26:52.675 --> 26:54.241
You say that now.

26:54.923 --> 26:56.278
Please don't shoot my stepfather.

26:56.279 --> 26:57.681
(BRAKES SQUEAL)

27:00.049 --> 27:01.782
Hey.

27:01.783 --> 27:03.147
Where's Dad at?

27:04.153 --> 27:06.253
Amantha had car trouble.

27:06.254 --> 27:08.228
There was a wrecker involved.

27:09.125 --> 27:10.692
That sucks.

27:10.693 --> 27:13.635
She was out on Clyetteville
Road by herself,

27:14.262 --> 27:16.800
just riding around, I guess.

27:18.233 --> 27:19.442
I'll be.

27:20.160 --> 27:22.680
I think she's smoking marijuana again.

27:24.715 --> 27:25.876
Huh.

27:28.711 --> 27:29.976
Who's the cake for?

27:31.013 --> 27:32.256
Daniel.

27:32.781 --> 27:33.949
Oh.

27:33.950 --> 27:35.384
His birthday?

27:35.385 --> 27:38.654
No. Just thought I'd send him a cake.

27:38.655 --> 27:40.355
No law against it.

27:42.011 --> 27:43.247
Hope not.

27:46.262 --> 27:48.296
How's he doing these days?

27:49.385 --> 27:52.033
He has a full-time job
now at a warehouse.

27:52.034 --> 27:53.934
He's still staying at
that halfway place.

27:54.945 --> 27:56.872
So, when can he have visitors up there?

27:56.873 --> 27:58.518
I mean, like family?

27:59.369 --> 28:01.300
Whenever he wants to, really.

28:02.854 --> 28:04.942
Oh. 'Kay.

28:06.066 --> 28:07.934
He's just not been up for it yet.

28:09.111 --> 28:12.253
I'm sure it's a lot, you
know, starting over...

28:12.254 --> 28:15.358
or starting, I guess, in this case.

28:19.095 --> 28:20.472
How was date night?

28:24.475 --> 28:26.934
Well, it's a little strange
at first, to be honest,

28:26.935 --> 28:29.070
meeting your wife on a date.

28:29.071 --> 28:30.146
I bet.

28:31.006 --> 28:32.690
But it's good to see her, too.

28:33.861 --> 28:35.476
I'm sure it is.

28:36.128 --> 28:40.248
Her therapist, she told us to
meet in a neutral place...

28:40.249 --> 28:43.620
you know, kind of avoid
certain triggers or whatever.

28:44.120 --> 28:47.198
It helps us, you know, practice
being more honest with each other.

28:47.924 --> 28:49.825
Kind of new age-y, but...

28:49.826 --> 28:52.461
Still, it sounds very challenging,

28:52.462 --> 28:57.667
trying to be honest
without all the baggage.

28:58.867 --> 29:02.418
♪♪

29:03.339 --> 29:05.094
It's kind of working for me, really.

29:05.907 --> 29:07.506
Hopefully Tawney, too.

29:11.179 --> 29:13.340
Takes a lot of courage
to do what you're doing.

29:15.050 --> 29:16.505
I'm proud of you.

29:16.985 --> 29:20.790
♪♪

29:30.767 --> 29:33.003
(WATER TURNING OFF AND ON)

29:47.418 --> 29:48.520
Can I...

29:49.405 --> 29:51.205
(CLICKS TONGUE) Can I
help you do anything?

29:51.879 --> 29:53.187
(CHUCKLES) Not bake a cake,

29:53.188 --> 29:56.499
but, uh, take out the
trash or something?

29:57.741 --> 30:01.097
Not right now. Thank you.
I'm still filling it up.

30:07.973 --> 30:09.235
I'm gonna turn in.

30:10.292 --> 30:12.793
- Night, Teddy.
- Night, Janet.

30:13.341 --> 30:17.146
♪♪

30:27.305 --> 30:28.889
Ole Billy Harris.

30:28.890 --> 30:30.478
Pretty good people, huh? (CHUCKLES)

30:31.628 --> 30:35.230
- Said he was carrying tonight.
- Well, some people do.

30:35.992 --> 30:37.652
That's politic of you.

30:37.653 --> 30:40.568
Not a subject gonna get a lot
of traction around here.

30:40.569 --> 30:42.228
Not the way you want it to.

30:43.633 --> 30:45.272
Are <i>you</i> carrying, Ted?

30:46.502 --> 30:47.943
I'll never tell.

30:47.944 --> 30:49.326
(SCOFFS)

30:50.712 --> 30:52.520
You want to come by the house tonight?

30:52.982 --> 30:54.549
I know your mother
would like to see you.

30:54.550 --> 30:56.318
This late?

30:56.319 --> 30:58.485
Well, you can stay the night,
see her in the morning.

30:59.429 --> 31:01.288
Why? What's wrong?

31:02.143 --> 31:03.558
She's just a little blue.

31:04.950 --> 31:09.499
- Mom's chronically blue.
- She's a little more than normal.

31:11.967 --> 31:13.353
Like before?

31:15.636 --> 31:17.606
She needs you right now, Amantha.

31:18.391 --> 31:22.167
She's the one that wanted
me to leave... leave town.

31:24.188 --> 31:26.524
He hasn't really
returned her calls much.

31:27.684 --> 31:29.417
That's kind of his M.O.

31:30.879 --> 31:34.544
And she's having a real hard time
letting go of certain things.

31:36.156 --> 31:37.733
Kind of <i>her</i> M.O.

31:40.396 --> 31:41.521
Anyway...

31:43.458 --> 31:44.895
you're her daughter.

31:45.400 --> 31:46.824
So...

31:47.535 --> 31:49.205
You pulled that out?

31:51.573 --> 31:53.375
I don't feel good about it.

31:54.377 --> 31:56.146
(CHUCKLES)

31:59.147 --> 32:00.594
(THUNDER RUMBLES)

32:02.420 --> 32:07.224
(INSECTS CHIRPING)

32:07.226 --> 32:11.797
(THUNDER CRASHES)

32:19.438 --> 32:23.243
(RAIN FALLING)

32:33.653 --> 32:35.555
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

32:35.556 --> 32:38.256
(RAIN TRICKLING)

32:38.257 --> 32:40.192
(SIGHS)

32:56.342 --> 32:58.578
(DOOR HINGES CREAK)

33:02.814 --> 33:04.188
Really, Mom?

33:05.115 --> 33:08.217
I just know he's soaking
wet in that old tent.

33:09.463 --> 33:11.150
(SIGHS)

33:11.620 --> 33:13.060
Does he have his phone with him?

33:13.086 --> 33:15.028
I made him take it, even
though he protested.

33:15.029 --> 33:15.674
(LAMP CLICKS)

33:15.675 --> 33:18.842
Well, why don't you call him
if it'll make you feel better?

33:19.339 --> 33:20.416
I'll get a lecture.

33:21.507 --> 33:22.876
Or not.

33:25.579 --> 33:27.415
You talk to Jon lately?

33:28.715 --> 33:30.649
It's 3:00 in the morning.

33:30.650 --> 33:32.584
(SIGHS)

33:32.585 --> 33:35.178
It just seems like I never even
get to talk to you anymore.

33:35.179 --> 33:36.414
I hardly see you.

33:36.415 --> 33:39.649
How about tomorrow or sometime
not in the middle of the night?

33:39.650 --> 33:41.651
You're not leaving early?

33:42.150 --> 33:44.720
- I don't have a car.
- Oh.

33:45.724 --> 33:47.125
Right.

33:47.126 --> 33:47.891
(SIGHS)

33:47.892 --> 33:50.561
I'm too old to be this poor.

33:50.562 --> 33:52.330
We'll figure something out, honey.

33:52.331 --> 33:55.968
(RAIN FALLING)

34:01.674 --> 34:03.509
That Willis boy is out.

34:06.645 --> 34:08.313
Out of what?

34:10.681 --> 34:11.777
Jail.

34:13.981 --> 34:15.588
Well, good for him.

34:17.688 --> 34:19.157
Yeah, good for him.

34:19.158 --> 34:20.757
(CLICKS TONGUE)

34:20.757 --> 34:23.092
He gets to see his
family and everything.

34:23.094 --> 34:26.364
(INHALES) I'm thrilled, in fact.

34:29.833 --> 34:33.638
♪♪

34:33.639 --> 34:35.475
He's gonna be okay, Mama.

34:38.141 --> 34:39.168
Who is?

34:41.362 --> 34:42.670
Jared.

34:45.851 --> 34:48.418
I know. (SIGHS)

34:48.420 --> 34:51.556
You're right. Good night.

34:56.328 --> 35:00.132
♪♪

35:07.873 --> 35:11.244
(PEEL CRUNCHING)

35:13.056 --> 35:14.845
A little bird said you
had a date last night.

35:14.846 --> 35:16.881
- I did, at that.
- (SILVERWARE CLATTERS)

35:16.882 --> 35:18.370
It go okay?

35:20.245 --> 35:22.574
Dad, I don't want to hurt your feelings.

35:23.049 --> 35:24.888
The harder you try to be
involved in my personal life,

35:24.889 --> 35:26.356
the more it makes me want to...

35:26.357 --> 35:28.627
(CHOPS) drink or something.

35:35.634 --> 35:38.237
- (LIQUID POURING)
- (SIGHS)

35:39.471 --> 35:41.539
(WHISK TAPPING)

35:41.540 --> 35:43.774
There's no time limit
on this Tawney thing.

35:43.775 --> 35:46.544
If there's any major
change, I'll let you know.

35:46.545 --> 35:48.546
Sounds good.

35:48.547 --> 35:50.615
AMANTHA: Oh, my.

35:50.616 --> 35:52.617
Are we having Big Ted's
famous flapjacks?

35:52.618 --> 35:54.684
Bringing back memories, isn't it?

35:54.685 --> 35:56.221
Brings back appetites.

35:58.790 --> 36:01.626
Lehman looked over
your car this morning.

36:01.627 --> 36:03.984
- Already?
- That's Lehman.

36:05.330 --> 36:06.564
And?

36:06.565 --> 36:09.200
The front-left control arm broke loose,

36:09.201 --> 36:10.770
and the axle dropped
right to the ground.

36:12.237 --> 36:13.803
Is that expensive?

36:13.804 --> 36:15.539
- It's not cheap.
- (SIGHS)

36:15.540 --> 36:18.642
He also felt that the transmission
was compromised, too,

36:18.643 --> 36:20.728
and a few other things
he's concerned about.

36:21.413 --> 36:22.946
Great.

36:22.947 --> 36:25.792
His suggestion is not to
throw good money after bad.

36:27.297 --> 36:28.385
(SIGHS)

36:28.386 --> 36:30.887
- Sorry.
- (DOOR HINGES CREAK)

36:30.888 --> 36:32.689
Hey.

36:32.690 --> 36:34.858
- If it isn't the intrepid adventurer.
- (DOOR CLOSES)

36:34.859 --> 36:36.394
Hardly.

36:36.395 --> 36:38.595
I'd hug you, but I've
already had a bath.

36:38.596 --> 36:40.664
I don't know how they
did it in the old days.

36:40.665 --> 36:42.265
It's hard to succeed at anything

36:42.266 --> 36:43.767
without the right equipment, buddy.

36:43.768 --> 36:46.671
We're just proud you took
the initiative to try it.

36:46.672 --> 36:48.407
- Absolutely.
- Yeah.

36:50.342 --> 36:51.610
It's not a fad.

36:56.714 --> 36:57.981
- All right, then.
- Okay.

36:57.982 --> 36:59.651
(DISHES CLATTER)

37:00.451 --> 37:03.188
(FORK CLINKS) Oh!

37:04.755 --> 37:07.792
Now I need a nap. So good.

37:07.793 --> 37:09.390
Yeah, buddy. Mm.

37:10.494 --> 37:11.562
Sure was, Ted.

37:11.563 --> 37:14.833
- May I, uh, be excused?
- Of course.

37:16.701 --> 37:17.937
(FOOTSTEPS DEPART)

37:19.871 --> 37:21.571
Okay.

37:21.572 --> 37:24.774
- Who is the unlucky chauffeur?
- I'll take you.

37:24.775 --> 37:27.010
- (SILVERWARE CLINKS)
- Come on.

37:27.011 --> 37:28.313
All right.

37:30.348 --> 37:32.483
Why don't you move
back here for a while?

37:32.484 --> 37:34.584
What?

37:34.585 --> 37:36.254
Just for a few months.

37:36.255 --> 37:39.289
You could save on a down payment
for a really good car...

37:39.290 --> 37:42.928
one you could feel safe in when
you do your riding around.

37:43.962 --> 37:45.796
(EXHALES)

37:45.797 --> 37:47.530
I still got a couple
months left on my lease,

37:47.531 --> 37:48.932
but even then...

37:48.933 --> 37:50.834
Well, maybe Marvin will
let you out of it early.

37:50.835 --> 37:52.503
Melvin. (CHUCKLES)

37:52.504 --> 37:54.838
But I doubt it. It's
not really his call.

37:54.839 --> 37:56.841
Or we could even loan you the money,

37:56.842 --> 37:57.975
and you could pay us back.

37:57.976 --> 37:59.776
Right, Ted?

37:59.777 --> 38:01.480
I'm sure we could work something out.

38:06.652 --> 38:09.820
I... I don't know.

38:09.821 --> 38:12.789
That's a lot of... steps,

38:12.790 --> 38:15.593
lot of owing, lot of
people in one place.

38:15.594 --> 38:17.061
We've all been in here before.

38:17.062 --> 38:18.729
Still trying to forget those years.

38:18.730 --> 38:20.666
Oh, you loved it.

38:22.619 --> 38:24.059
It's just an option.

38:26.151 --> 38:28.071
I appreciate the offer, Mom.

38:28.072 --> 38:30.274
(SMOOCHES) Really.

38:31.273 --> 38:33.059
Flapjacks were the best ever.

38:34.045 --> 38:35.512
Glad you liked them.

38:36.438 --> 38:37.782
After you.

38:37.783 --> 38:38.983
(FOOTSTEPS DEPART)

38:38.984 --> 38:41.420
Bye-bye, y'all. (SIGHS)

38:45.424 --> 38:47.390
AMANTHA: Still got your big-ass truck?

38:47.391 --> 38:49.859
- No, I got a Prius.
- (LAUGHS)

38:49.860 --> 38:51.330
(DOOR CLOSES)

38:55.389 --> 38:58.656
- I'll clean up.
- Well, I can help.

39:02.406 --> 39:03.792
I'm going to Nashville.

39:05.317 --> 39:06.472
Okay.

39:07.752 --> 39:10.533
(SHAKILY) Stand outside
that house if I have to.

39:11.449 --> 39:15.761
I have to see him, make sure he's real.

39:17.419 --> 39:19.725
I think that's a good idea.

39:24.795 --> 39:26.830
It was nice of you to make flapjacks.

39:28.335 --> 39:30.557
(SIGHS) Kind of like the old days.

39:31.628 --> 39:35.060
I mean, our old days.

39:35.806 --> 39:39.611
♪♪

39:43.013 --> 39:45.082
TED JR.: I love what you've
done with the place.

39:45.083 --> 39:46.582
AMANTHA: Yeah, right.

39:47.485 --> 39:50.620
(KEYS JINGLE)

39:50.621 --> 39:52.622
Hey, does this grill outside work?

39:52.623 --> 39:53.879
Never tried it.

39:55.726 --> 39:57.561
- You hate everyone who lives here?
- (DOOR OPENS)

39:57.562 --> 39:59.998
Pretty much.

40:04.469 --> 40:06.504
I got a proposition.

40:06.505 --> 40:07.699
Okay.

40:08.641 --> 40:09.996
Let's trade places.

40:11.095 --> 40:12.075
What?

40:12.076 --> 40:14.812
You go stay with your
mother, and I come here.

40:14.813 --> 40:16.414
Don't you have a mortgage?

40:16.415 --> 40:18.649
You've got, what, two
months left on your lease?

40:18.650 --> 40:19.910
Thereabouts.

40:21.111 --> 40:23.553
So, I come here, I'll
pay half your rent,

40:23.554 --> 40:26.055
and in two months, you've got
close to 1,000 bucks saved up

40:26.056 --> 40:28.024
for a down payment on a
car, free and clear.

40:28.025 --> 40:29.794
Why would I pay half the rent?

40:29.795 --> 40:31.746
Because you need a car, and I don't.

40:32.292 --> 40:33.745
But you need something.

40:35.801 --> 40:37.200
Not really.

40:37.201 --> 40:39.937
I hope you don't sell tires like this.

40:40.864 --> 40:42.027
Okay.

40:42.773 --> 40:46.824
Truth is, I never thought I'd
be at the house this long.

40:47.545 --> 40:50.513
I come home, there's Dad.
I go to work, there's Dad.

40:50.514 --> 40:51.988
On the weekends, there's Dad.

40:52.616 --> 40:56.787
- I can't do it anymore.
- So, I would be doing you the favor?

40:57.607 --> 40:58.722
It'd be mutual.

40:59.298 --> 41:00.890
Wouldn't pay half the
rent, tell you that.

41:00.891 --> 41:02.760
- 25%?
- Hell, no.

41:02.761 --> 41:05.196
If you stay here, you
pay the rent in full.

41:05.197 --> 41:07.308
Okay. (SIGHS) I'll pay the rent.

41:08.632 --> 41:09.867
(SCOFFS)

41:09.868 --> 41:12.001
God, let me think about it first.

41:12.002 --> 41:13.966
I gotta go.

41:14.534 --> 41:17.106
Dad would fall all over himself
to take you to work every day.

41:17.107 --> 41:18.575
That's 'cause he's a gentleman.

41:18.576 --> 41:21.512
Come on, I can't be late. I'm the boss.

41:21.513 --> 41:22.847
Bullshit.

41:22.848 --> 41:23.914
AMANTHA: Yeah, I know.

41:23.915 --> 41:25.364
(DOOR OPENS)

41:26.083 --> 41:27.785
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

